Class KeyIteratorEmptyTests

java.lang.Object
myTest.KeyIteratorEmptyTests
public class KeyIteratorEmptyTests extends Object
Test case for KeyIterator when the underlying map is empty. This class tests the behavior of KeyIterator methods when there are no elements in the map.
See Also:
  • MapAdapter
  • MapAdapter.KeySet
  • MapAdapter.KeyIterator
Design
This test is designed to ensure that the KeyIterator behaves correctly when the underlying map is empty, specifically checking the hasNext(), next(), and remove() methods.
Libraries
JUnit 4.13, Hamcrest 1.3

    • setUp

      public void setUp()
      Setup method to initialize the map and keySet before each test. This method is called before each test to ensure a fresh state.

    • testStartToFinish

      public void testStartToFinish()
      Test to verify that hasNext() returns false when the iterator is empty.
      Design
      This test is designed to ensure that the KeyIterator behaves correctly when the underlying map is empty.
      Description
      This test checks that the KeyIterator does not have any elements to iterate over by counting the number of iterations.
      Preconditions
      The map must be empty before this test runs.
      Postconditions
      The KeyIterator should not have any elements.
      Expected Results
      The test should pass if the iteration count equals 0.

    • testRemoveAll

      public void testRemoveAll()
      Test to verify that the empty iterator has no elements to remove.
      Design
      This test is designed to verify that an empty KeyIterator behaves correctly when attempting to iterate and remove elements.
      Description
      This test checks that an empty KeyIterator has no elements to iterate over and that the underlying map remains empty.
      Preconditions
      The map must be empty before this test runs.
      Postconditions
      The map should remain empty after this test runs.
      Expected Results
      The test should pass if no iterations occur and the map remains empty.

    • testRemoveWithoutNext

      public void testRemoveWithoutNext()
      Test to verify that remove() throws IllegalStateException when called without a preceding call to next().
      Design
      This test is designed to ensure that the KeyIterator does not allow removal of elements without first calling next().
      Description
      This test checks that calling remove() without a prior call to next() results in an IllegalStateException.
      Preconditions
      The map must be empty before this test runs.
      Postconditions
      The KeyIterator should remain unchanged after this test runs.
      Expected Results
      The test should pass if remove() throws an IllegalStateException.
